Default case: just use template and do not change its value in the MN configuration dialog
1st case: use template and change value via MN configuration dialog
2nd case: use template and change value via flow variable
3rd case: template contained in other template and config changed in dialog
Tests if metanode updates retain the configuration set on instances of that wrapped metanode template.
The bug reverted the configuration of the quickform nodes to what it is in the main template.
The test will first load the workflow, perform NO update, run the worklfow and expect all difference checkers on the left
to be green and on the right to be red. It then performs an update, runs the workflow again and then expects the left
side to be red/failed and right side to be all green.
